This paper focuses on improving the reliability of NAND flash memory through various architectural techniques. It involves experimental characterization and designing new flash controller algorithms, which falls under the category of computer systems and architecture (cs.AR). The paper also deals with managing flash retention and error characteristics, which can be categorized under systems and control (cs.SY) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DC). Additionally, the paper discusses the underlying flash device characteristics and workload behavior, which can be classified under embedded systems (cs.ET) and software engineering (cs.SE).
